casebody.data:
Sidney M. HAUPTMAN, Trustee of the Charles Nelson Co., a Corporation, Debtor, Appellant, v. WELLS FARGO BANK & UNION TRUST CO., a Corporation, and UNION SECURITIES CORPORATION, Appellees. No. 8863. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Dec. 18, 1939. Sterling Carr, of San Francisco, Cal., for appellant. Sidney M. Ehrman, Albert M. Monaco and Heller, Ehrman, White & McAuliffe, all of San Francisco, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, DENMAN, and MATHEWS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to stipulation of counsel for respective parties, and good cause therefor appearing, ordered appeal in above cause dismissed, that a decree of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
